{
  "texts": [
    "Almost all research domains were more inclined toward more traditional ML algorithms as opposed to neural networks.",
    "When looking at traditional ML algorithms aside from SVMs, Information Technology used Ensemble and Decision Tree models, which are models that usually require hyperparameter optimization, more often than other domains.",
    "While both Psychology and Education used simple models such as Linear, Nearest Neighbors, and LDA & QDA models.",
    "When focusing on neural networks, Healthcare and Information Technology were the two domains with increased neural network usage, as opposed to Education, which was the domain with the least usage of neural networks.",
    "Figure 9B shows the distribution of the best-performing supervised learning algorithms with respect to the five research domains."
  ]
}